<paragraph blockId="14.[192,874,1904,1929]" box="[192,874,1904,1929]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,375,1904,1928]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<typeStatus box="[192,260,1904,1928]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[382,515,1904,1928]" genus="Syrichthus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,515,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Syrichthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[sic] 
<emphasis box="[580,659,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">festiva</emphasis>
Erichson, [1849].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1441,217,401]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,217,241]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister genus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, 1895" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1895" box="[559,988,217,241]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sostrata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[559,663,218,241]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Sostrata</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, 1895
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1004,1065,218,242]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Type</typeStatus>
species. 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1876" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leucochitonea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scintillans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Leucochitonea scintillans</emphasis>
Mabille, 1876
</taxonomicName>
, which is treated as a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Menetries, 1829))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Menetries" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sostrata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis box="[1061,1292,249,273]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Sostrata bifasciata</emphasis>
(Ménétriés, 1829))
</taxonomicName>
, where these species were placed before (
<figureCitation box="[772,844,281,305]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="16.[192,275,1178,1200]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,214,1144]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[192,1440,213,1144]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 6. Genomic trees of Erynnini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677247" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677247/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Keys to E.42.1a in 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1094,1257,281,305]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1895" box="[258,362,314,337]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sostrata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[258,362,314,337]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Sostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by blue ventral hindwing, broader wings and in male genitalia by longer harpe, clearly separated from the rest of valva. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly276665.9.3:C95G, aly923.23.1:G274A, aly 
<date box="[736,845,377,401]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="2790-03-06">2790.3.6</date>
:A367C, aly923.23.1:T688G, aly2101.22.7:A31C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,417,474]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,417,441]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, given for the 
<typeStatus box="[1238,1291,418,442]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
species and for the festive looks that distinguish this genus from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1895" box="[841,945,450,473]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sostrata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[841,945,450,473]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Sostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,489,577]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,428,489,513]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[485,538,490,514]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName box="[641,908,489,513]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leucochitonea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronion">
<emphasis box="[641,908,489,513]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Leucochitonea cronion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C and R. Felder, 1867, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille and Boullet, 1917" authorityName="Mabille and Boullet" authorityYear="1917" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pythonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulans">
<emphasis box="[1184,1440,489,513]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Pythonides caerulans</emphasis>
Mabille and Boullet, 1917
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1898" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1898" box="[527,1013,521,546]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pythonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adamantinus">
<emphasis box="[527,834,521,545]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Pythonides adamantinus</emphasis>
Mabille, 1898
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1953" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1953" box="[1026,1381,521,545]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sostrata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grippa">
<emphasis box="[1026,1218,522,545]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Sostrata grippa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1227,1381,521,545]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans, 1953</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1953" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1953" box="[192,529,553,577]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sostrata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jinna">
<emphasis box="[192,368,554,577]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Sostrata jinna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[375,529,553,577]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans, 1953</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,965,593,618]" box="[192,965,593,618]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,593,617]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe Erynnina Brues and Carpenter, 1932.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1441,633,785]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,340,633,657]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Comments.</emphasis>
Although this genus does not disrupt monophyly of the former concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1895" box="[1181,1280,634,657]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sostrata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1181,1280,634,657]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Sostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that included these species, genetic distance between these sister genera is not less than that between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindsey" authorityYear="1925" box="[1277,1440,666,689]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Potamanaxas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1277,1440,666,689]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Potamanaxas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin, 2019" authorityName="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2019" box="[245,333,698,721]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anaxas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[245,333,698,721]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Anaxas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[348,430,698,722]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, or between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1894" box="[582,657,697,721]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Mylon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[582,657,697,721]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Mylon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1824" box="[718,826,698,721]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anastrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[718,826,698,721]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Anastrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This comparatively large genetic differentiation is present in both nuclear and mitochondrial genomes. The two genera are also clearly diagnosed by wing patterns and shapes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
